==Finnish==

===Noun===
'''krapula'''

# [[hangover]] 

===Etymology===

From Latin [[crapula]].

===Usage notes===

Mostly ''krapula'' comes in the morning, after drinking too much [[alcohol]], but the term is also semi-officially used for [[withdrawal]] symptoms caused by the wearing off of another [[intoxicant]]s or [[medication]]. 

Also see [[krapularyyppy]], [[viinakramppi]], [[loiventava]]

